name: Seabed Entanglement
description: Is the seabed inert matter or the ocean's skin? The starfish can be considered the ebb and flow of soft and hard tissues in complex structures that are, in turn, part of larger seabed patterns. Entwined and utterly interwoven with the other species that blanket the ocean floor, they live, grow and regrow. Their regenerative capacities further blur the line between the soft and hard, living and inert, the ocean and the earth. What if to touch the ocean required us to become entangled between water and sediment, to be one of many intertwined?
